         first concrete planned emitter, per M-INC §1 IDENTIFY.
         The EoI engine
         (`~/code/algorithms/eoi-engine.md`) is a candidate
         secondary emitter — `eoi_instances[]` writes from engine
         runs map cleanly onto `state/spawned` + `link/asserted`
         events (e.g. parent/child instance relations as observed
         in `vsat-poc-2026-q2-q3-scenario-c-vsatlatarium` 2026-05-25).]
    next[Cross-mission consumers (per claude-1 downstream finding
         2026-05-26): substrate-2 sorry-typing
         (M-action-cost-modelling §3.2) adopts the 7-status
         `state/*` set as `:sorry`-entity-status vocabulary;
         M-a-sorry-enterprise mining-track resumes emit-into-substrate
         using this vocabulary; `:sorry/r3d-per-entity-attribution`
         (`futon2/data/sorrys.edn`) re-types as
         `:mission`-scale, consuming this vocabulary as the shared
         status surface.]
    next[Granularity-enum extension (deferred to step (c)): EoI
